"So Fine" is the first single off reggae artist Sean Paul's upcoming album, Imperial Blaze. The track was premiered on April 25, 2009 on his official website.

The video will premiere on Sean Paul's official site. It was directed by Ray Kay in Miami. The video premiered on June 24, 2009.

Imperial Blaze is the upcoming fourth studio album by reggae artist, Sean Paul. The album is set to be released on August 18, 2009.

The album was originally scheduled to be released in the summer of 2007 under the name The Next Thing, but was then pushed back to November 2008.

Sean Paul told MTV that he wants to be less focused on party songs such as Get Busy, We Be Burnin', and Temperature. He said he wants his songs to focus on youth violence in Jamaica

The album's title means "Kings Fire". Sean Paul commented on the title saying,

    "I'm not the king. I'm the fire, I'm the flame, I'm the energy."

In an interview with DJ Swerve, Sean Paul confirmed that he did 60 tracks for the album, with 21 tracks making the final cut. He also revealed some of the song titles that will be on the album: "Don't Tease Me", "Press It Up", "Lift It", "She Want Me", "Lately", "Hold My Hand", "Pepperpot", "Now That I Got You", "Birthday Suit" and "She Wanna Be Down".

The song "Watch Dem Roll" was released in 2007 and was said to be the first single off his new album. However, Sean Paul premiered the official first single, "So Fine", on April 25, 2009 via his official website.
